OC:mah]\n200956:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: D-gluconate + acceptor = 2-dehydro-D-gluconate + reduced acceptor.\" [RHEA:12769]\n200994:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a (2R)-hydroxycarboxylate + acceptor = a 2-oxocarboxylate + reduced acceptor.\" [RHEA:23664]\n201010:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-2-hydroxy-2-phenylacetate + acceptor = 2-oxo-2-phenylacetate + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.1.99.31]\n201111:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: an aldehyde + H2O + acceptor = a carboxylate + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.2.99.7]\n201189:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 6-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)-7,8-dioxo-1,2,3,4,7,8-hexahydroquinoline-2,4-dicarboxylate + 3 O2 = 2 H2O + 2 H2O2 + H+ + pyrroloquinoline quinone.\" [EC:1.3.3.11, RHEA:10692]\n201555:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: sucrose + acceptor = 3-dehydro-alpha-D-glucosyl-beta-D-fructofuranoside + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.1.99.13]\n202017:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 1,4-benzoquinone + H2O + phenylacetyl-CoA = 2 hydroquinone + phenylglyoxylyl-CoA.\" [RHEA:15705]\n202040:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA + H2O + acceptor = (24R,25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha,24-tetrahydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.17.99.3]\n202147:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3,3',5'-triiodo-L-thyronine + iodide + acceptor + H+ = L-thyroxine + acceptor-H2.\" [RHEA:18897]\n205393:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3-hydroxyaminophenol = aminohydroquinone.\" [EC:5.4.4.3, RHEA:20577]\n230496:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: L-tyrosine + S-adenosyl-L-methionine + reduced acceptor = 2-iminoacetate + 4-methylphenol + 5'-deoxyadenosine + L-methionine + acceptor + 2 H+.\" [EC:4.1.99.19, GOC:crds, MetaCyc:RXN-11319, PMID:17403671]\n231064:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: formate + a quinone = CO2 + a quinol.\" [GOC:bhm, RHEA:48592]\n252105:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + dihydroflavodoxin + [formate C-acetyltransferase]-glycine = 5'-deoxyadenosine + L-methionine + flavodoxin semiquinone + [formate C-acetyltransferase]-glycin-2-yl radical.\" [EC:1.97.1.4, GOC:jl, PMID:18307109]\n257276:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 6-decylubiquinone + 2 thiosulfate = 6-decylubiquinol + tetrathionate.\" [RHEA:10936]\n271752:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-methylsulfanyl-N(6)-dimethylallyladenosine(37) in tRNA + acceptor-H2 + O2 = N(6)-[(2E)-4-hydroxy-3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl]-2-(methylsulfanyl)adenosine(37) in tRNA + acceptor + H2O.\" [PMID:8253666, RHEA:65812]\n291453:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: phylloquinol + a protein with a disulfide bond = phylloquinone + a protein with reduced L-cysteine residues.\" [RHEA:57744]\n291467:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3-hydroxy-2-methyl-3-phytyl-2,3-dihydronaphthoquinone + oxidized dithiothreitol + H2O = 2,3-epoxy-2,3-dihydro-2-methyl-3-phytyl-1,4-naphthoquinone + 1,4-dithiothreitol.\" [RHEA:21560]\n291604:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H(2) + menaquinone = reduced menaquinone.\" [EC:1.12.5.1, RHEA:18641]\n292064:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: AH2 + O2 + phylloquinone = 2,3-epoxyphylloquinone + A + H2O.\" [RHEA:16745]\n292082:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 O2 + donor-H2 + Latia luciferin = light + H2O + acceptor + formate + CO2 + oxidized Latia luciferin.\" [EC:1.14.99.21]\n292316:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a quinone + an aldehyde + H2O = a carboxylate + a quinol + H+.\" [RHEA:13881]\n294092:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3-O-N-acetyl-D-galactosalaminyl-[protein] + UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine = 3-O-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl-[protein] + UDP. Linkage of the glycan to the protein occurs via the oxygen atom in the side chain of an L-serine or L-threonine residue.\" [EC:2.4.1.147]\n294372:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a hydroxyanthraquinone + UDP-D-glucose = a glucosyloxyanthraquinone + UDP.\" [EC:2.4.1.181]\n298795:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (-)-quinate + pyrroloquinoline-quinone = (-)-3-dehydroquinate + pyrroloquinoline-quinol.\" [RHEA:23672]\n299169:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-2-hydroxyglutarate + acceptor = 2-oxoglutarate + reduced acceptor.\" [RHEA:21252]\n299547:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a 3-oxo-5-beta-steroid + acceptor = a 3-oxo-D4-steroid + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.3.99.6]\n299595:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a 3-oxosteroid + acceptor = a 3-oxo-D1-steroid + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.3.99.4]\n300721:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: alizarin + UDP-D-glucose = 1-hydroxy-2-(beta-D-glucosyloxy)-9,10-anthraquinone + H+ + UDP.\" [EC:2.4.1.103, RHEA:20677]\n300737:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: primary alcohol + acceptor = aldehyde + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.1.99.20, MetaCyc:ALKAN-1-OL-DEHYDROGENASE-ACCEPTOR-RXN]\n302168:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: cellobiose + acceptor = cellobiono-1,5-lactone + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.1.99.18, MetaCyc:CELLOBIOSE-DEHYDROGENASE-ACCEPTOR-RXN]\n302667:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: an aldehyde + acceptor + H2O = a carboxylate + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.2.99.6, MetaCyc:CARBOXYLATE-REDUCTASE-RXN]\n303693:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: D-sorbitol + acceptor = L-sorbose + reduced acceptor.\" [RHEA:21320]\n304795:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a ubiquinone + keto-D-fructose = 5-dehydro-D-fructose + a ubiquinol.\" [RHEA:22304]\n305088:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2,5-dihydroxybenzoate + H+ = CO2 + hydroquinone.\" [EC:4.1.1.62, RHEA:21312]\n315227:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 juglone + O2 = 2 3,5-dihydroxy-1,4-naphthoquinone + 2 H+.\" [PMID:4041238, RHEA:18745]\n315290:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: kynurenate + donor-H2 + O2 = 7,8-dihydro-7,8-dihydroxykynurenate + acceptor.\" [EC:1.14.99.2]\n315507:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: L-pipecolate + acceptor = delta1-piperideine-6-carboxylate + reduced acceptor. Delta1-piperideine-6-carboxylate is also known as 2,3,4,5-tetrahydropyridine-2-carboxylate.\" [EC:1.5.99.3, MetaCyc:L-PIPECOLATE-DEHYDROGENASE-RXN]\n317115:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: NADH + H+ + a quinone = NAD+ + a quinol.\" [RHEA:46160]\n318696:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: pyridoxine + acceptor = isopyridoxal + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.1.99.9, MetaCyc:PYRIDOXINE-5-DEHYDROGENASE-RXN]\n319462:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: spermidine + acceptor + H2O = 1,3-diaminopropane + 4-aminobutanal + reduced acceptor.\" [EC:1.5.99.6, MetaCyc:SPERMIDINE-DEHYDROGENASE-RXN]\n319685:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: L-lysine + NAD+ = L-1-piperideine-6-carboxylate + NH4+ + NADH + 2 H+. (S)-(2-aminoethyl)-L-cysteine can act as a substrate, and NADP+ can act as the acceptor.\" [EC:1.4.1.18]\n320703:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-seryl-[tyrosine-3-monooxygenase] = ADP + H+ + O-phospho-L-seryl-[tyrosine-3-monooxygenase].\" [EC:2.7.11.6]\n320899:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: uracil + acceptor = barbiturate + reduced acceptor.\" [RHEA:22752]\n321438:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: an acceptor + NH4+ + H2O = hydroxylamine + a reduced acceptor + H+.\" [RHEA:22052]\n322663:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: hydroquinone + UDP-D-glucose = H+ + hydroquinone O-beta-D-glucopyranoside + UDP.\" [EC:2.4.1.218, RHEA:12560]\n324430:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-hydroxy-1,4-benzoquinone + 2 H+ + NADH = benzene-1,2,4-triol + NAD+.\" [RHEA:12428]\n324492:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: trichloroethene + chloride + acceptor = tetrachloroethene + reduced acceptor. The reaction occurs in the reverse direction.\" [RHEA:20353]\n337142:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-methyl-6-phytyl-1,4-benzoquinone + S-adenosyl-methionine = 2,3-dimethyl-6-phytyl-1,4-benzoquinone + S-adenosyl-homocysteine.\" [MetaCyc:RXN-2542]\n337153:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-methyl-6-solanyl-1,4-benzoquinone + S-adenosyl-methionine = 2,3-dimethyl-6-solanyl-1,4-benzoquinone + S-adenosyl-homocysteine.\" [MetaCyc:RXN-2762]\n339855:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-2-hydroxyglutarate + acceptor = 2-oxoglutarate + reduced acceptor.\" [RHEA:38295]\n345624:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + thymine + acceptor = 5-methyl-barbiturate + donor-H2.\" [RHEA:13469]\n346632:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2,3,6-trichlorohydroquinone + 2 glutathione = 2,6-dichlorohydroquinone + glutathione disulfide + HCl.\" [PMID:1459949, RHEA:56832]\n347041:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 4 hydroquinone + O2 = 4 benzosemiquinone + 4 H2O.\" [EC:1.10.3.2]\n347374:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a ubiquinone + H2O + pyruvate = a ubiquinol + acetate + CO2.\" [EC:1.2.5.1]\n347597:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: oxidized coenzyme F420-(gamma-L-Glu)(n) + a quinol + H+ = reduced coenzyme F420-(gamma-L-Glu)(n) + a quinone.\" [PMID:10971593, PMID:8055920, RHEA:39663]\n374005:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: gluconapin + a reduced electron acceptor + O2 = progoitrin + an oxidized electron acceptor + H2O.\" [PMID:18945935, RHEA:60628]\n377435:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) + a quinone = S0 (sulfane sulfur) + a hydroquinone.\" [RHEA:30239]\n384005:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: protoporphyrinogen IX + acceptor = protoporphyrin IX + reduced acceptor.\" [GOC:mah, PMID:19583219]\n384016:name: menaquinone-dependent protoporphyrinogen oxidase activity\n384018:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: protoporphyrinogen IX + menaquinone = protoporphyrin IX + reduced menaquinone.\" [GOC:mah, PMID:19583219]\n410286:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a brassinosteroid + 3'-phosphoadenosine-5'-phosphosulfate = sulfated brassinosteroid + adenosine-3',5'-diphosphate. This reaction is the transfer of a sulfate group to the hydroxyl group of a brassinosteroid acceptor, producing the sulfated brassinosteroid derivative.\" [PMID:10409637, PMID:17039368]\n433021:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: nitrite + acceptor = product(s) of nitrate reduction + reduced acceptor.\" [GOC:dos, GOC:jh]\n439588:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-lactate + an ubiquinone = pyruvate + an ubiquinol.\" [PMID:10944213, PMID:4575624, RHEA:51468]\n439751:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3-chlorobenzoate + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = 3-chlorobenzoate-cis-3,4-diol + an oxidized electron acceptor.\" [PMID:38488372, PMID:8285670]\n439759:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3,4-dichlorobenzoate + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = 3,4-dichlorobenzoate-cis-4,5-diol + an oxidized electron acceptor.\" [GOC:pz, PMID:9322760]\n444150:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (9Z)-octadecenoate + AH2 + O2 = (12R)-hydroxy-(9Z)-octadecenoate + acceptor + H2O.\" [RHEA:55956]\n445172:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (+)-costunolide (12,6alpha) + reduced [NADPH-hemoprotein reductase] + dioxygen = 3beta-hydroxycostunolide + oxidized [NADPH-hemoprotein reductase] + H2O.\" [MetaCyc:RXN-15533]\n446065:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: O2 + 2 an ubiquinol = 2 H2O + 2 an ubiquinone.\" [GOC:pz, RHEA:30255]\n446184:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: typhasterol + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = castasterone + H2O + an oxidized electron acceptor.\" [GOC:pz, PMID:17138693]\n448305:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: isoorientin + an L-rhamonsylated rhamnosyl acceptor = isoorientin 2'-O-rhamnoside + a non rhamnosylated rhamnosyl acceptor.\" [GOC:pz, PMID:15220389]\n448677:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (9Z,12Z)-hexadecadienoyl-CoA + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = 9,12,15-cis-hexadecatrienoyl-CoA + 2 H2O + an oxidized electron acceptor.\" [EC:1.14.19.13]\n449081:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a menaquinone + NADH + H+ = a menaquinol + NAD+.\" [RHEA:29235]\n449104:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + a [ribosomal protein S12] L-aspartate89 + a sulfurated [sulfur carrier] + a reduced electron acceptor = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + L-methionine + 5'-deoxyadenosine + 2 H+ + a [ribosomal protein S12] 3-methylthio-L-aspartate89 + an unsulfurated [sulfur carrier] + an oxidized electron acceptor.\" [EC:2.8.4.4, GOC:pz]\n449116:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + an aldose + an oxidized electron acceptor = H+ + an aldonate + a reduced electron acceptor.\" [GOC:pz, MetaCyc:RXN0-6371, PMID:16864586]\n454303:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a quinone + glutathione + H+ + hydrogen sulfide = a quinol + S-sulfanylglutathione.\" [RHEA:55156]\n460871:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a 3-demethylubiquinone + S-adenosyl-L-methionine = a ubiquinone + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.\" [PMID:38425362, RHEA:81215]\n461006:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: Fe(II)-heme o + 2 acceptor + H2O = Fe(II)-heme a + 2 acceptor-H2. The conversion of heme o to heme a occcurs by two successive hydroxylations of the methyl group at C8 using water as the oxygen source. The first hydroxylation forms heme i, the second hydroxylation results in an unstable dihydroxymethyl group, which spontaneously dehydrates, resulting in the formyl group of heme A.\" [PMID:30397130, RHEA:63388]\n461122:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a ubiquinone + NADH + H+ = a ubiquinol + NAD+.\" [RHEA:23152]\n466097:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: tryptamine + reduced acceptor + O2 = 4-hydroxytryptamine + acceptor + H2O.\" [PMID:28763571]\n469557:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-2-hydroxyglutarate + a quinone = 2-oxoglutarate + a quinol.\" [PMID:30498244, RHEA:58664]\n470387:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a quinone + D-glucose = a quinol + D-glucono-1,5-lactone.\" [RHEA:47372]\n472415:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: R-CH + a halogen + oxygen donor = R-C-halogen +H2O.\" [PMID:28466644, PMID:34368824]\n479719:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a quinol + nitrate = a quinone + H2O + nitrite.\" [RHEA:56144]\n480243:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a 5-methoxy-2-methyl-3-(all-trans-polyprenyl)benzoquinone + NADH + O2 = a 3-demethylubiquinone + NAD+ + H2O.\" [PMID:23445365, PMID:38425362, RHEA:81211]\n591180:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a flavonoid + 3'-phosphoadenosine-5'-phosphosulfate = sulfated flavonoid + adenosine-3',5'-diphosphate. This reaction is the transfer of a sulfate group to the hydroxyl group of a flavonoid acceptor, producing the sulfated flavonoid derivative.\" [PMID:23611783]\n594789:def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a (2R)-2-hydroxycarboxylate + a quinone = a 2-oxocarboxylate + a quinol.\" [PMID:3013300, PMID:4582730, RHEA:11272]\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
